issue.title: Fakespot - Retry Shopping API after 500 errors doesn't work

labels.name: Bug 🐞
labels.description: This is a bug with existing functionality not behaving as expected

labels.name: S3
labels.description: Blocks non-critical functionality and a work around exists

issue.body:
## Steps to reproduce
1. Setup Fiddler (or other proxy that allows you to change the response status code before the response hits the app client)
2. Simulate a 500 response status for all requests to https://mozilla-ohttp-fakespot 
3. From the app client open the drawer for a product 
4. Check the number of the requests the client sends when 500 status code is received 

### Expected behavior
The client app retries the call 3 times 

### Actual behavior
The client app doesn't retry 

### Device & build information
* Device: iOS simulator, iPhone 14+ <!--- iPhone model, iOS version -->
* Build version: V9000 (35002) <!--- Visit Settings and scroll down to find the version number -->
* First seen version: V9000 (35002)  <!--- Is this new to this version or have you seen it before? -->
### Notes
Attachments: 
<!--- Screenshots or screen recordings are very helpful for reproducing! -->

issue.title: Clearing all browsing history does not appear to work

labels.name: Bug 🐞
labels.description: This is a bug with existing functionality not behaving as expected

labels.name: S2
labels.description: Major Functionality/product severely impaired and a satisfactory workaround doesn't exist

issue.body:
## Steps to reproduce
1. Go to History
1. Click the bin icon
1. Click "Everything"

Context: I'm currently trying to reduce the size of "Documents & Data" as reported by iOS (since Firefox has the largest size and I am running out of storage).

### Expected behavior
Browsing history is deleted (and thus space is freed up).

### Actual behavior
Browsing history still appears, and there is no confirmation the deletion has occurred.

### Device & build information
* Device: iPhone SE (first generation), iOS 15.7.8
* Build version: 116.4 (33723)
* First seen version: Unknown (this has always been the case for me)

### Notes
To attempt to reduce storage, I have disabled History sync to my Firefox account. I would expect this to mean that I can delete the local history, but that it does not affect my other synced devices.

I am raising this separately to #16234 in case the deletion mechanism is different between the two screens.



┆Issue is synchronized with this [Jira Spike](https://mozilla-hub.atlassian.net/browse/FXIOS-7311)

comment.body: When I was logged into my account I also wasn't syncing history, so I wonder if the syncing settings aren't respected in some way?

issue.title: Rearranging tabs results in sharp corners despite rounded tab shape

labels.name: Bug 🐞
labels.description: This is a bug with existing functionality not behaving as expected

issue.body:
## Steps to reproduce
* Open the tab tray
* Drag a tab to rearrange it
    1. Expected behavior
Tab retains rounded shape even while rearranging
    1. Actual behavior
Sharp corners appear on the tab, colored blue if the dragged tab was the active tab or black if the tab was inactive
    1. Device & build information
* Device: iPhone 12
* Build version: Firefox Daylight 103.0 (13910)
